FBIS3-51675 "drlat015_o_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 Colombia Acting Defense Minister Comments PA2301203794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 23 Jan 94 PA2301203794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "NTC News" newscast] [Text] As the military sector sees it, the Apartado massacre is a product of the ongoing political war in that region, a problem that is taking root in spite of the military reinforcements sent there. [Begin acting Defense Minister General Ramon Emilio Gil Bermudez recording] The violent ones want to impose, at all costs and against the people's will, things they cannot impose through arguments. [end recording] As General Gil sees it, this carnage mirrors the cruelty levels the guerrillas have reached. [Gil] They vented their fury on peasants in La Chinita neighborhood. Names of people were called from a list and then they were mercilessly murdered. [end recording] The victims were participating in a political demonstration to back Hope, Peace, and Liberty Senator Anibal Palacios.
